window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>In this middle grade novel-in-verse by the Newbery Medal-winning and Coretta Scott King Honor Award-winning author of <i>The Crossover</i>, soccer, family, love, and friendship take center stage as 12-year-old Nick learns the power of words when he wrestles with problems at home, stands up to a bully, and tries to impress the girl of his dreams. Helping him along are his best friend and sometimes teammate, Coby; and The Mac, a rapping librarian who gives Nick inspiring books to read. </p> <p>This electric and heartfelt novel-in-verse by poet Kwame Alexander bends and breaks as it captures all the thrills and setbacks, action and emotion of a World Cup match! </p>"; 
